cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with resource allocation and coexistence mechanisms in LTE-U systems, which are wireless communication networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper proposes a novel deep learning approach for modeling the resource allocation problem, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also formulates a noncooperative game model, which could place it in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper aims to achieve fairness with existing WiFi networks and other LTE-U operators, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with maximizing the total served LTE-U traffic load, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory).
